# {{PLUGIN_NAME}}

A plotdesk plugin.

## Installation

This plugin is installed via the plotdesk Plugin Management UI:
1. Go to Platform Admin > Plugins
2. Connect your GitHub account (if not already connected)
3. Select this repository and click "Install"

## Development Setup

```bash
composer install
npm install
```

## Frontend Build

This plugin uses `@plotdesk/plugin-vite` to build frontend assets. Vue and Inertia are externalized and provided by the plotdesk host application at runtime — your bundle stays small.

```bash
npm run build        # Build to dist/ (must be committed!)
npm run dev          # Watch mode during development
```

Configure your pages and payloads in `vite.config.js`:

```js
import { plotdeskPlugin } from '@plotdesk/plugin-vite';

export default plotdeskPlugin({
  pages: {
    'MyPage': './resources/js/Pages/MyPage.vue',
  },
  payloads: {
    'MyPayload': './resources/js/Payloads/MyPayload.vue',
  },
});
```

## Structure

```
{{PLUGIN_SLUG}}/
  plugin.json                # Plugin manifest (apps, permissions, navigation, interfaces)
  composer.json              # PHP dependencies (plotdesk/plugin-sdk)
  package.json               # Frontend dependencies (@plotdesk/plugin-vite)
  vite.config.js             # Frontend build config
  tailwind.config.js         # Tailwind CSS config
  src/
    {{PLUGIN_STUDLY}}Plugin.php    # Service provider (routes, events, commands)
    Apps/
      {{PLUGIN_STUDLY}}/
        {{PLUGIN_STUDLY}}App.php   # AI function definitions
    Http/Controllers/              # Controllers for custom pages
    Models/                        # Eloquent models
  routes/web.php             # Web routes (auto-prefixed with /plugins/{{PLUGIN_SLUG}}/)
  resources/
    js/Pages/                # Vue page components
    js/Payloads/             # Vue payload components (rich chat output)
    lang/                    # Translations
  database/migrations/       # Migrations (tables must be prefixed: {{PLUGIN_SLUG}}_*)
  vendor/                    # PHP dependencies (committed!)
  dist/                      # Pre-built frontend assets (committed!)
```

## Important Rules

- `vendor/` and `dist/` are **committed to git** — no build steps run on the target server
- `node_modules/` is **not** committed (only needed for local development)
- Database tables must be prefixed with `{{PLUGIN_SLUG}}_`
- After `composer install/update` → commit `vendor/`
- After `npm run build` → commit `dist/`

## AI Function Development

Edit `src/Apps/{{PLUGIN_STUDLY}}/{{PLUGIN_STUDLY}}App.php` to add AI functions. Each function:
- Is declared in `getFunctions()` with name, description, and parameters
- Has a handler method in StudlyCase (e.g., `search_contacts` → `SearchContacts`)
- Returns a string that the AI uses as context
- Can use `$message->attachPayload()` for rich UI rendering
- Can use `$message->setLoading()` / `removeLoading()` for loading states

## Using AI in Your Plugin

```php
use App\Plugins\Support\PluginAi;
use App\Plugins\Support\PluginChat;

// Direct AI call (simple, no platform context)
$result = PluginAi::call($team, 'You are a translator.', 'Translate: Hello', 'plugin:{{PLUGIN_SLUG}}:translate');

// Programmatic chat (full platform context — apps, silos, tables, etc.)
$result = PluginChat::run($team, $groupId, 'Analyze the latest sales data', 'plugin:{{PLUGIN_SLUG}}:analysis');
```

## Configuration

Plugin settings are defined in `plugin.json` under `apps[].setting_fields`. Admins configure them per team and group in the plotdesk App Settings.
